comments: Kuzma (WAS) releases from Russell (LAL) as both players briefly engage and disengage prior to receiving the incoming pass.
Russell (LAL) establishes himself in Bagley III's (WAS) path and collapses his arms as he absorbs the incoming contact during the screen.
Kuzma (WAS) contests Russell's (LAL) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Bagley III (WAS) briefly grasps Davis' (LAL) jersey as both players engage during the rebound.
Poole (WAS) is drawn into the air on the pump fake by Reaves (LAL) and initiates contact to Reaves' face that affects his SQBR.
James (LAL) establishes himself in Poole's (WAS) path and is firming up when he absorbs the incoming contact during the pick.
Kuzma (WAS) briefly places his hand to Davis' (LAL) body as he starts his dribble, which he is able to move through before the shot attempt.
Kuzma (WAS) turns to roll and incidental contact occurs with Reaves (LAL) as Reaves goes under the pick.
Hachimura (LAL) legally contests Poole's (WAS) jump shot attempt.
Russell (LAL) establishes himself in Kuzma's (WAS) path and absorbs the incoming contact during the pick.
Bagley III (WAS) maintains verticality and absorbs the ensuing contact when he cleanly blocks James' (LAL) driving shot attempt.
Bagley III (WAS) cleanly deflects the incoming inbounds pass as he defends Davis (LAL).
The ball is last touched by Bagley III (WAS) prior to it going out of bounds.
Davis (LAL) is established in Poole's (WAS) path when he absorbs the incoming contact during the pick.
Reaves (LAL) releases the shot attempt prior to landing.
Reaves (LAL) commits a take foul on Poole (WAS).
James (LAL) briefly places his hand to Poole's (WAS) body at the start of his dribble, which he is able to move through.
James (LAL) legally contests Poole's (WAS) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Avdija (WAS) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Bagley III (WAS) briefly places his hand to Russell's (LAL) body at the start of the drive, which he is able to move through.
Jones (WAS) lowers his arm and initiates contact with Russell's (LAL) wrist that affects his driving shot attempt.

Russell (LAL) initiates contact to Avdija's (WAS) lower body during the drive that affects his SQBR.  The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Reaves (LAL) is moving alongside Poole's (WAS) path and the body contact that occurs as they come together during the drive is marginal.

Replay review of the foul called on James (LAL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Avdija (WAS) extends his arm and delivers contact to James (LAL) that dislodges him from his legally obtained defensive position during the drive.
Reaves (LAL) slightly extends his arms within the frame of his body and makes contact with Kuzma (WAS) during the pick, which is marginal as it does not affect Kuzma's ability to defend.

Reaves (LAL) initiates the contact with Poole (WAS) as the two players engage off ball and the contact is marginal.  Poole disengages and moves towards the basket, but does not dislodge Reaves from his defensive position.
Kuzma (WAS) moves laterally into James' (LAL) path and initiates contact to his body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Avdija (WAS) brushes Hachimura's (LAL) arm as he controls the rebound as the contact that occurs is marginal.
Poole (WAS) briefly places his hand to Reaves' (LAL) side as he attempts to establish a screening position and then releases.
Poole (WAS) contests Reaves's (LAL) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Hachimura (LAL) maintains a legal guarding position as he moves alongside Kuzma's (WAS) path to the basket.
Reaves (LAL) blocks Poole's (WAS) jump shot attempt.
Avdija (WAS) is moving alongside James' (LAL) path and as marginal contact occurs as they come together at the end of the drive.
Poole (WAS) brushes Reaves' (LAL) body at the start of the drive as he is able to move through the contact, which is marginal.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: The ball deflects off Davis' (LAL) foot prior to it going out of bounds.
Bagley III (WAS) slightly extends his arm into Dinwiddie's (LAL) body during the screen, which is marginal and does not affect his ability to defend.
Hachimura (LAL) legally contests Kuzma's (WAS) jump shot attempt.
